================================================================================
Cachy-Void is a fusion: Void's FORM and CachyOS's SUBSTANCE. So is its licensing.
================================================================================

FORM (this repository's own code) — the BSD 2-Clause license above.
The Cachy-Void installer, the update engine, and all the tooling in this
repository are BSD-2-Clause — the same permissive license Void Linux uses for
its own `void-packages` build system, which this project overlays. Minimal,
permissive, no strings. That is the Void form.

SUBSTANCE (what the tooling builds) — the upstream copyleft licenses, unchanged.
This project only orchestrates; it relicenses nothing. The performance artifacts
it produces carry their own terms:

  * `linux-cachy` is a derivative work of the Linux kernel  ->  GPL-2.0-only.
  * The BORE scheduler patch it applies
    (https://github.com/firelzrd/bore-scheduler)             ->  GPL-2.0.
  * Every package rebuilt from the overlay allowlist retains its own upstream
    license; only the compiler flags change, not the license.

Building, running, or redistributing those artifacts is governed by their own
(copyleft) terms. That is the CachyOS substance — honored, not collapsed into
permissive. Neither philosophy is given up: permissive form, copyleft substance.
